article.headline: Tennessee Tech 72, E. Illinois 53
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie had 15 points to lead Tennessee Tech to a 72-53 Ohio Valley Conference win over Eastern Illinois on Thursday night. Daniel Northern had 12 points and 10 rebounds, Frank Davis added 11 points and Anthony Fisher chipped in 10 points for Tennessee Tech (3-6, 1-1), which opened the game with a 15-0 run and never trailed. Eastern Illinois (1-7, 0-1) didn't score until well over six minutes into the first half and trailed the Golden Eagles 42-21 at the break on 23 percent shooting. The Panthers tried to come back in the second half, but a 11-4 run by Tennessee Tech over the final four minutes put the game well out of reach. Romain Martin led the Panthers with 20 points. Bobby Catchings added 12 points and 10 rebounds.
